\begin_layout Chapter
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Given six parameters comprising three angles and three distances, determine
 the conventions for combining these parameters that is most consistent
 with available independent exterior orientation data.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
OriMania explores brute force combinations of the 6 unknown parameters utilized
 in the context with various common conventions for expressing rigid body
 orientations.
 It evaluates each candidate to determine which one(s) most closely match
 independently determined relative orientation data.
\end_layout

