\begin_layout Section
Transform Parameter Combinations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Attitude may be expressed by a unitary spinor product of the form,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
e^{\gamma C}e^{\beta B}e^{\alpha A}
\]

\end_inset

where each of the (spin) angle sizes, 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha,\beta,\gamma$
\end_inset

, correspond (in some order or another) with the three angle size values
 available a priori, and each of the unitary bivector directions, 
\begin_inset Formula $A,B,C$
\end_inset

, correspond with a plane of rotation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
NOTE: Here it is assumed that the planes of rotation are associated with
 standard Cartesian basis planes (and not, for example, some arbitrary combinati
on of directions in space
